<subSubSection id="C31766C1FFDFFFC972A8FCE1FEB5E11B" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB2354AFFDFFFC972A8FCE1FEB5E11B" blockId="12.[151,1127,821,1037]" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B979E958FFDFFFC972A8FCE1FEFAE65B" bold="true" box="[151,262,821,845]" pageId="12" pageNumber="61">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the most modified genus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4EC9FFDFFFC970B8FCE1FD0DE65B" authorityName="Carayon" authorityYear="1954" box="[647,753,821,845]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Scolopini">Scolopini</taxonomicName>
. The ostiolar peritreme is probably the most characteristic of all 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4EC9FFDFFFC973E1FC81FD88E67B" box="[478,628,853,877]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Anthocoridae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9C48BBFFDFFFC970BDFC81FCB2E67B" author="CARPINTERO D. L." box="[642,846,853,877]" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" pagination="25 - 44" refId="ref7334" refString="CARPINTERO D. L. 2002: Catalogue of the Neotropical Anthocoridae (Heteroptera). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina 61: 25 - 44." type="journal article" year="2002">CARPINTERO (2002)</bibRefCitation>
transferred this genus to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4EC9FFDFFFC972A8FCA1FEDBE69B" authorityName="Carayon" authorityYear="1972" box="[151,295,885,909]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Lasiochilinae">Lasiochilinae</taxonomicName>
based on the shape of ostiolar peritreme, straight with dorsal half of metapleura smooth. However, here we restore its position according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9C48BBFFDFFFC9717DFC41FC09E6BB" author="CARAYON J." box="[834,1013,917,941]" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" pagination="309 - 349" refId="ref7300" refString="CARAYON J. 1972: Caracteres systematiques et classification des Anthocoridae (Hemipt.). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, N. S. 8: 309 - 349." type="book chapter" year="1972">CARAYON (1972)</bibRefCitation>
. The male genitalia have never been described; unfortunately, the single male we studied had lost the pygophore, and we could not study genital structures but we could see the typical uradenia of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4EC9FFDFFFC972E4FC21FEB9E11B" authorityName="Carayon" authorityYear="1954" box="[219,325,1013,1037]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Scolopini">Scolopini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
